aa(lp69
VIf you know anything about government technology,
p70
aVyou know that this isn't how it normally goes.
p71
aVProcuring software usually takes a couple of years.
p72
aVWe had a team that worked on a project in Boston last year
p73
aVthat took three people about two and a half months.
p74
aVIt was a way that parents could figure out
p75
aVwhich were the right public schools for their kids.
p76
aVWe were told afterward that if that had gone through normal channels,
p77
aVit would have taken at least two years
p78
aVand it would have cost about two million dollars.
p79
aVAnd that's nothing.
p80
aVThere is one project in the California court system right now
p81
aVthat so far cost taxpayers
p82
aVtwo billion dollars,
p83
aVand it doesn't work.
p84
aVAnd there are projects like this
p85
aVat every level of government.
